		<text id="text01" x="24" y="50" width="348" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;As you saw in the video on the previous page, neurons rapidly produce new synapses during early childhood, about twice as many as the adult brain will need to work efficiently. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Rapid neural branching happens in different parts of the brain at different times. Most of it occurs during the first 24 months of life. These new connections are tied to various aspects of development:&lt;/P&gt;</content>
		</text>
